    <Statements>
      <Statement>Express a fraction with denominator 10 as an equivalent fraction with denominator 100, and use this technique to add two fractions with respective denominators 10 and 100.&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;i&gt;For example, express 3/10 as 30/100, and add 3/10 + 4/100 = 34/100&lt;/i&gt;.</Statement>
    </Statements>
